cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.IT

The paper proposes a data-driven technique using a neural network design for local fiber reconstruction in the human brain using DW-MRI. This involves the use of deep learning and image processing techniques, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which are a subset of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the optimization of the network using null space deep learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the use of information theory (cs.IT) to improve the reproducibility and generalizability of the model.
